04/11/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Authorities in the central town of Kraljevo declared an emergency situation Wednesday (November 3rd) after an earthquake measuring 5.4 on the Richter scale rocked the area. 
Two people were killed and dozens were injured in the quake. 
Some parts of town are still without water and electricity. 
President Boris Tadic visited the area and promised to help. 
The government is allocating 47,000 euros in short-term aid earmarked for reconstruction. 
Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic said that further assistance will be allocated after the damage is fully evaluated.
Meanwhile, an earthquake measuring 3.2 on the Richter scale shook Zagreb on Wednesday; its epicentre was about 20km southwest of the capital. 
No damage or injuries were reported. 
(RTS, Beta, Tanjug - 03/11/10)
